First, we describe the principle of employing PL spectra to determine dopant profiles of boron-diffused regions. Figure 1a shows dopant profiles, measured by the ECV technique, of a selected set of boron-diffused calibration samples. As the boron-rich layer was removed before the final thermal drive-in process (i.e. the dopant source is finite), each dopant profile can be fitted with a Gaussian function33:1N(z)=Np×exp[−(z−zp)2zf2]\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
